The paper deals with cross-media retrieval between images and text, which is a topic related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves jointly optimizing the correlation between images and text, which is a task related to natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for visual feature extraction, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a new model for cross-media retrieval, which involves learning mappings between different modalities, a task related to machine learning (cs.LG).
